00:22:51.072 --> 00:22:54.371
itself increases GDF15.

381
00:22:55.412 --> 00:22:55.772
Right.

382
00:22:56.572 --> 00:22:56.952
Have you ever done-

383
00:22:56.992 --> 00:22:58.992
Yes. No, we haven't done that. We haven't done.

384
00:22:59.052 --> 00:23:02.212
What we have done is we've taken mice with the

385
00:23:02.512 --> 00:23:06.232
adipocyte-specific PHGDH knockout and put

386
00:23:06.292 --> 00:23:10.032
them on an obesogenic diet, and they also

387
00:23:10.072 --> 00:23:10.741
gain weight,

388
00:23:11.792 --> 00:23:15.392
albeit not as quite as fast as the normal mice.

389
00:23:15.892 --> 00:23:17.392
But we haven't done the experiment you suggest.

390
00:23:17.412 --> 00:23:19.292
That's a good experiment, and we could try that.

391
00:23:19.332 --> 00:23:19.912
I'll definitely-

392
00:23:20.072 --> 00:23:20.892
Easy experiment.

393
00:23:20.952 --> 00:23:21.252
Yes.

394
00:23:21.292 --> 00:23:24.712
And the other thing is just simply, what's the mechanism

395
00:23:25.632 --> 00:23:29.102
by which when you take these amino acids out of the

