1367
01:18:04.688 --> 01:18:08.608
And we saw that this new dietary pattern has

1368
01:18:08.668 --> 01:18:11.888
a very strong correlation with the established diet,

1369
01:18:12.948 --> 01:18:16.808
as you can see here, a positive correlation with Western diet and negative

1370
01:18:16.908 --> 01:18:19.668
correlation with prudent, healthy diet.

1371
01:18:20.088 --> 01:18:23.208
Indicating that by using the CRC-associated

1372
01:18:23.668 --> 01:18:27.648
microbes as the single response variable, we can

1373
01:18:27.728 --> 01:18:30.348
identify a dietary pattern that

1374
01:18:31.028 --> 01:18:34.548
recapitulates the general healthy versus

1375
01:18:34.608 --> 01:18:36.108
unhealthy dietary pattern.

1376
01:18:36.908 --> 01:18:39.428
And when we apply this score to our

1377
01:18:39.728 --> 01:18:43.428
population-based cohorts, we say this

1378
01:18:43.768 --> 01:18:47.708
dietary score has a positive association with colon cancer risk.

1379
01:18:48.088 --> 01:18:52.048
This is after adjusting for various risk factors for colon

1380
01:18:52.128 --> 01:18:52.508
cancer.

1381
01:18:54.408 --> 01:18:58.028
And also, most strikingly, when we separate the colon

1382
01:18:58.108 --> 01:18:59.088
cancer into

1383
01:19:00.348 --> 01:19:03.748
subtypes according to the presence of the tissue bacteria,

1384
01:19:04.608 --> 01:19:08.408
we saw the CRC microbial diet score

1385
01:19:08.468 --> 01:19:12.128
showed a much stronger association with colon cancer risk

1386
01:19:12.328 --> 01:19:16.168
among for CRCs that have positive

1387
01:19:16.308 --> 01:19:20.008
bacteria in the tumor tissue. Again, this indicates

1388
01:19:20.068 --> 01:19:23.716
thatCR's diet may indeed

1389
01:19:24.856 --> 01:19:27.916
play an important role by modulating the microbiome.

1390
01:19:30.896 --> 01:19:34.756
So to summarize the findings from research question two on top of

1391
01:19:34.796 --> 01:19:38.576
the first question, so we believe that

1392
01:19:38.716 --> 01:19:42.216
diet and lifestyle is really driving the microbial changes

1393
01:19:42.336 --> 01:19:42.856
along the

1394
01:19:43.656 --> 01:19:45.876
colon cancer development sequence.

1395
01:19:48.016 --> 01:19:51.716
So the last question, what are the role of the individual dietary

1396
01:19:51.836 --> 01:19:54.996
