1435
01:22:11.506 --> 01:22:14.136
And also we are collecting other biospecimens.

1436
01:22:16.056 --> 01:22:19.806
And in terms of the relationship of coffee with the microbiome,

1437
01:22:20.376 --> 01:22:24.086
this is a study that we published last year in collaboration with Dr.

1438
01:22:24.356 --> 01:22:28.216
Nicolas Getta from Italy, and we saw a very strong and

1439
01:22:28.716 --> 01:22:31.616
a specific impact of coffee on the microbiome.

1440
01:22:32.376 --> 01:22:36.316
So first, when we rank all the individual dietary factors

1441
01:22:36.356 --> 01:22:39.836
